    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** serving as our clear offensive anchor. With an elite efficiency score of 80.98, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** benefits from an incredibly favorable matchup against Chase Petty (xERA 6.57). His ability to exploit the wind conditions and his dynamic platoon advantage make him a high-floor start despite his usual spot in the bottom of the order. Following closely is **Carson Benge** (67.24) and **Trea Turner** (66.43), both of whom offer massive upside due to favorable park factors and leadoff positioning, respectively. While **Carson Benge** carries a 34% rain risk, his favorable matchup against Tomoyuki Sugano suggests that he remains a must-start unless a total washout occurs.\n\nManaging the perimeter of our lineup required a difficult decision at the bench spot. **Caleb Durbin** narrowly missed the final cut with a score of 39.11; while his stolen base potential is historically enticing, his matchup against a high-tier arm like Tarik Skubal (xERA 2.76) significantly suppressed his projected efficiency, forcing him below our 40-point threshold. We continue to monitor the status of **Christian Yelich** and **Lars Nootbaar**, both of whom remain on the IL, while **Zac Veen** is still rostered in the minors. Elsewhere, **Yordan Alvarez** remains a locked-in starter despite a tough draw against Yoshinobu Yamamoto, as his elite 0.427 xwOBA provides enough statistical insulation to warrant confidence in his 60.60 score. \n\nStrategic concerns linger for **Hyeseong Kim** and **Colt Keith**, who both suffer from neutral-to-negative platoon impacts against southpaw starter Payton Tolle. While **Hyeseong Kim** remains in the lineup due to his opportunistic potential against Tolle's slower delivery\u2014which boosts his stolen base profile by 4%\u2014his score of 41.47 is dangerously close to our bench floor. We are keeping a close watch on official lineup postings for **Gary Sanchez**, **Dillon Dingler**, **Kazuma Okamoto**, **Chase Meidroth**, **Junior Caminero**, **Kyle Schwarber**, **Luke Raley**, **Josh Smith**, **Luis Pena**, and **Pedro Ramirez** to ensure that our assumed batting orders hold firm and that no late-scratch risks compromise our daily scoring capacity.",
